181.subject: UGST
181.courseDescription: First Year Seminar. Credit 0 to 3. Seminar on various contemporary topics; introduction to high quality college instruction and research; focus on writing, speaking, discussion and research; open to all majors; restricted to first-time-in-college students and limited in size to provide small class experience. May be taken two times for credit.

sections.subject: UGST
sections.courseTitle: SEM THIS POTATO OR THAT POTATO

182.subject: UGST
182.courseDescription: Topics in Undergraduate Studies.  Credit 0 to 3. Selected interdisciplinary topics related to specific programs as identified by the office of undergraduate studies; for students in approved first year programs. May be taken two times for credit. Prerequisite: Freshman classification or approval of instructor.

285.subject: UGST
285.courseDescription: Directed Studies. Credit 0 to 4. Directed individual study on selected topics in undergraduate studies. May be taken six times for credit.

484.subject: UGST
484.courseDescription: Internship.  Credit 0 to 3. Directed internship in a community, public or private organization to provide students with on-the-job training and/or applied research experience appropriate to career objectives. May be taken three times for credit. Prerequisites: Junior or senior classification and approval of instructor.

485.subject: UGST
485.courseDescription: Directed Studies. Credit 0 to 4. Directed individual study on selected topics in undergraduate studies. May be taken six times for credit.

491.subject: UGST
491.courseDescription: Research.  Credit 0 to 4. Research conducted under the direction of a faculty member in undergraduate studies. May be taken three times for credit. Prerequisites: Junior or senior classification and approval of instructor.

492.subject: UGST
492.courseDescription: Cooperative Education in Public Policy. Credit 0 to 3. Educational work assignment in public policy setting related to student's career interest and course of study; supervision of the student will be by the cooperating employer and the instructor; reports, approved by course instructor, will be required. May be taken two times for credit. Prerequisites: Junior or senior classification and participation in Public Policy Internship Program.
